<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-19T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-19T15:00:00-05:00" n="111" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G Economic and Financial
                                Problems/17: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hull</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-19T17:00:00-03:00">December 19, 1933—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 19—3:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>74. It is highly desirable here and now to add confidence and realism
                                to the situation by taking the initial step in respect of
                                multilateral action carrying out my economic resolution which the
                                Conference has adopted. Accordingly I wish to introduce into the
                                Conference, urging signature prior to adjournment, a general
                                agreement pledging the parties not to invoke the most-favored-nation
                                clause of bilateral treaties to obtain the advantages of
                                multilateral economic treaties. The text is substantially as
                                contained in air mail letter December 8, McClure to Hawkins,<note n="43" xml:id="d111fn43">Not printed.</note> though somewhat
                                strengthened and improved.</p>
                            <p>Immediate authorization will be appreciated.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>